<paragraph id="3340217A40185F33FF50FD764D003E4C" blockId="15.[162,778,763,1582]" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840185F33FF50FD764EB03B72" box="[162,468,763,785]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">
Diagnosis – male 
<typeStatus id="EC449FD840185F33FE9DFD714EAA3B72" box="[367,462,763,784]" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">holotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
Face as 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940185F33FDA5FD714DAD3B72" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[599,713,763,784]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlosii">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840185F33FDA5FD714DAD3B72" box="[599,713,763,784]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">C. carlosii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but lateral vittae distinct from eye to mouth (
<figureCitation id="ABC43DFF40185F33FD48FC904D9F3B52" box="[698,763,794,816]" captionStart="Figures 7–10" captionStartId="5.[159,249,1648,1667]" captionTargetBox="[169,1432,196,1601]" captionTargetId="figure-77@5.[159,1439,188,1615]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 7–10. Adult Copestylum, lateral view of the head; scale line = 3.5 mm. 7. Copestylum carlosii sp. nov., female holotype; 8. Copestylum volcanorum sp. nov., male holotype; 9. Copestylum barbara sp. nov., male holotype; 10. Copestylum elizabethae sp. nov., male holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5429846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5429846/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); mesonotum as 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940185F33FEA2FCB34EA63B2F" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[336,450,824,846]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlosii">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840185F33FEA2FCB34EA63B2F" box="[336,450,824,846]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">C. carlosii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; scutellum yellow and black haired; pleura mainly black, only yellowish on the dorsal part of the anepisternum, posterior anepimeron, and katatergum and katepimeron; wings extensively microtrichose, and medial crossveins infused black; legs mainly black, except pale at apices of femorae and ventral surface of tibiae and tarsi; legs black haired; abdominal tergites 1–4 black with pale yellow side spots; tergite 1 pale haired, tergite 2 with white hairs on side spots and posterior margin with a band of black hairs, tergites 3 and 4 black haired; sternites 1 and 4 black, sternites 2 and 3 yellow; sternites whitehaired; genitalia – surstylus broad and rectangularshaped with distal margins tapered; lower superior lobe of hypandrium more like a rounded projection than hook-like; hypandrium without lateral projections and aedeagus with smooth apical margin (
<figureCitation id="ABC43DFF40185F33FF58FAC84E3F3D3A" box="[170,347,1346,1368]" captionStart="Figures 32–40" captionStartId="19.[162,252,1764,1783]" captionTargetBox="[282,1322,201,1729]" captionTargetId="figure-126@19.[275,1330,196,1732]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 32–40. Adult Copestylum, male genitalia; right and left-hand figures scale line = 0.50 mm, for middle column figures, left-hand scale line = 0.85 mm. 32–34. Copestylum tacanense sp. nov., male holotype: 32. genitalia and associated structures, lateral view; 33. epandrium, ventral view; 34. surstylus, ventral view. 35–37. Copestylum tapanti sp. nov., male holotype: 35. genitalia and associated structures, lateral view; 36. hypandrium, ventral view; 37. surstylus, ventral view. 38–40. Copestylum volcanorum sp. nov., male holotype: 38. genitalia and associated structures, lateral view; 39." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5429856" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5429856/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">Figs 38, 39, 40</figureCitation>
); female – similar to 
<typeStatus id="EC449FD840185F33FD96FAC84DA13D3A" box="[612,709,1346,1368]" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">holotype</typeStatus>
male except for colour pattern of abdomen, which is black with a pair of large, square-shaped, white spots on tergite 2, and abdomen white-haired; sternites black except the sternite 2 and the anterior margin of sternite 3, which are yellowish; width of the vertex about 13.3% width of head. Length: body, 10.00– 
<quantity id="F4078C9F40185F33FF50F9924E713E4C" box="[162,277,1560,1582]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.08" pageId="15" pageNumber="282" unit="mm" value="10.8">10.80 mm</quantity>
; wing, 
<quantity id="F4078C9F40185F33FE94F9924D633E4C" box="[358,519,1560,1582]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.899999999999999" metricValueMax="9.1" metricValueMin="8.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="282" unit="mm" value="8.899999999999999" valueMax="9.1" valueMin="8.7">8.70–9.10 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis id="018BFD6840185F33FDEAF9934D483E4C" box="[536,556,1561,1582]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">N</emphasis>
= 2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A40185F33FF50F9CD4AE9397A" blockId="15.[162,778,1606,1904]" lastBlockId="15.[826,1442,196,280]" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840185F33FF50F9CD4D453E3E" box="[162,545,1606,1628]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="282">Diagnosis – larva and puparium:</emphasis>
Suckers present on abdominal segments 1–6; marginal band complete, including both thorax and abdomen; anal segment with two pairs of long, narrow lappets above the marginal band; ventral surface of lobes coated with setae; anterior spiracles present; vestiture of dark papillae bearing groups of setae; ventral surface of anal segment with dark papillae bare of setae; posterior breathing tube dark brown to black, elongate such that length of tube below transverse ridge is more than twice the length of tube above the ridge, three pairs of spiracular openings that are curved in shape; pupal spiracles black with openings almost to base.
</paragraph>
